value.title: Biden speaks with Netanyahu after delay raised questions
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden spoke Wednesday with his Israeli counterpart Benjamin Netanyahu, ending what had been a lengthy stretch without a call after Biden took office.

value.title: Biden, Israeli PM Netanyahu have 'warm and friendly' talk
value.excerpt: President Biden spoke with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu on Wednesday, Netanyahu’s office confirmed to Fox News.

value.title: Pence: Rush Limbaugh was a 'giant,' inspired me to enter talk radio
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Mike Pence called Rush Limbaugh a "giant" who inspired Pence to enter talk radio in the 1990s, a move that helped lead to a successful political career.

value.title: New York Times: Trump Pentagon officials delayed promotions of female generals due to fear over Trump's reaction
value.excerpt: Promotions of two female generals were delayed by Pentagon officials until after the 2020 presidential election out of fear of "turmoil" from President Donald Trump's White House, The New York Times reported Wednesday.

value.title: Biden wants to put a Black woman on the Supreme Court, putting spotlight on lack of diversity in lower courts
value.excerpt: Biden has vowed to pick a Black woman for the Supreme Court. Advocates say he must also address the lack of diversity in the nation's lower courts.

value.title: Trump impeachment manager says she's filled with 'glee' at prospect of questioning McCarthy about Capitol riot
value.excerpt: Del. Stacey Plaskett said she is filled with "glee" at the prospect of questioning House Minority Leader Kevin McCarthy regarding a phone call between him and former President Donald Trump during the Capitol riot in January.

value.title: Donald Trump mourns passing of Rush Limbaugh: ‘He is a legend, he loved this country so much'
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump joined Fox News to remember conservative radio host Rush Limbaugh, who died at age 70 following a lung cancer battle.

value.title: U.S. conservative radio provocateur and Trump ally Rush Limbaugh dies
value.excerpt: Provocative and polarizing U.S. talk radio luminary Rush Limbaugh, a leading voice on the American political right since the 1980s who boosted, and was honored by, former President Donald Trump, has died at age 70 after suffering from lung cancer,

value.title: Iran's Khamenei demands 'action' from Biden to revive nuclear deal
value.excerpt: Supreme Leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei demanded "action, not words" from the United States if it wants to revive Iran's 2015 nuclear deal with world powers, challenging new President Joe Biden to take the first step toward a thaw.

value.title: WATCH: Trump Plaza in Atlantic City is demolished
value.excerpt: Videos show the moment former President Donald Trump's long-standing Trump Plaza in Atlantic City is destroyed in a controlled demolition. The casino and hotel were closed in 2014.

value.title: Trump Plaza casino in Atlantic City to be demolished
value.excerpt: The long-vacant Trump Plaza casino in Atlantic City, N.J., once a symbol of the glitz and glamor of the high-rolling lifestyle, was slated to be reduced to a pile of rubble on Wednesday.

value.title: Kamala Harris pressed on school reopenings, says teachers 'should be a priority' in receiving COVID vacccine
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris said the Biden administration believes teachers "should be a priority" in receiving the coronavirus vaccine as parents and educators clash over whether it is safe for teachers to return to the classroom without inoculations against COVID-19.

value.title: Explainer: What is the Ku Klux Klan Act cited in lawsuit against Trump
value.excerpt: The Democratic chairman of the House Homeland Security Committee has filed a lawsuit against former President Donald Trump that cites a little-known federal statute that was first passed after the Civil War.

value.title: "Duped" and "egged on": Capitol rioters use Trump as excuse in court

value.title: Biden dismisses a Democratic plan to wipe out $50,000 in federal student-loan debt
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden supports $10,000 in loan forgiveness, far less than Sens. Elizabeth Warren and Chuck Schumer proposed earlier this year.

value.title: Biden says he feels 'a sense of history' living at White House
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden on Tuesday described the "sense of history" he feels residing at the White House and all the ways living in the historic building is an adjustment, including being waited on by White House staff.

value.title: White House to freeze out Mohammed bin Salman, Saudi prince who was close to Trump White House
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden is recalibrating U.S. diplomatic relations with Saudi Arabia, deploying a new approach that includes sidestepping Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman, who had a close relationship with the Trump administration.

value.title: Trump, ex-campaign manager Brad Parscale, meet at Mar-a-Lago: Source
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump met Tuesday with former campaign manager Brad Parscale at his Mar-a-Lago resort in Palm Beach, Florida, a source familiar with the matter told Fox News.

value.title: Trump calls McConnell a ‘political hack’ as GOP divide deepens post-impeachment
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump blistered Mitch McConnell as a “political hack," following McConnell’s speech calling Trump responsible Capitol riot.

value.title: Biden administration urges DHS officials to stop using ‘illegal alien’ in favor of ‘inclusive’ language
value.excerpt: The Biden administration is urging officials at the Department of Homeland Security to stop using phrases like “illegal alien” in favor of what it says are more “inclusive” terms -- part of a broader effort by the administration to change language use on immigration.

value.title: Plaskett insists Trump will 'never be elected again' despite impeachment acquittal
value.excerpt: Rep. Stacey Plaskett says Republicans made a calculation to save their political futures rather than convict Donald Trump.

value.title: Giuliani no longer representing Trump 'in any legal matters,' adviser says
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump's longtime personal attorney, Rudy Giuliani, is "not currently representing President Trump in any legal matters," senior Trump adviser Jason Miller told CNN on Tuesday.

value.title: Democrats and Biden prepare to unveil bill that would provide a pathway to citizenship for undocumented immigrants
value.excerpt: The Biden administration, in concert with Hill Democrats, is preparing to unveil legislation this week that seeks to provide a pathway to citizenship to the 11 million undocumented immigrants living in the United States.

value.title: Biden to press for Covid-19 relief package during CNN's Wisconsin town hall
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden, no longer encumbered by his predecessor's impeachment trial and eager to seize the national spotlight, will bring the case for his massive coronavirus relief plan to the country on Tuesday when he participates in a CNN town hall at 9 p.m. ET in Milwaukee.
